"ISic001313. Epitaph for Markia Loukilia","\u003Cdiv id=\"editions\">\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Μαρκία\n                    Λουκιλία\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Μαρκία\">Μαρκία\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Λουκιλία\">Λουκιλία\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"χρηστὰ\">χρηστὰ\u003C/span> · \u003Cspan data-text=\"καὶ\">καὶ\u003C/span> ἄ-\u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>μεμτος · \u003Cspan data-text=\"αἴζωσἔζωσεν\">αἴζωσ(εν)\u003C/span>  \u003Cbr id=\"al5-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"ἔτιαἔτη\">ἔτια\u003C/span> εἴκοσι´ \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">l.3 reg., orig. ἄμεμτος | l.4 reg., orig. ΑΙΖΩΣαἴζωσ | l.5 reg., orig. ΕΤΙΑἔτια\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Μαρκία\n                    Λουκιλία\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Μαρκία\">ΜΑΡΚΙΑ\u003C/span>\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Λουκιλία\">ΛΟΥΚΙΛΙΑ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"χρηστὰ\">ΧΡΗΣΤΑ\u003C/span>·\u003Cspan data-text=\"καὶ\">ΚΑΙ\u003C/span>Α\u003Cbr id=\"al4-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>ΜΕΜΤΟΣ·\u003Cspan data-text=\"αἴζωσἔζωσεν\">ΑΙΖΩΣ\u003C/span>\u003Cbr id=\"al5-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"ἔτιαἔτη\">ΕΤΙΑ\u003C/span>ΕΙΚΟΣΙ\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">l.3 reg., orig. ἄμεμτος | l.4 reg., orig. ΑΙΖΩΣαἴζωσ | l.5 reg., orig. ΕΤΙΑἔτια\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001313_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic001313_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001313.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic001313-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text based on photographs\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 4\">line.4: \u003Cspan>Torremuzza, Ferrara, Bertucci, Franz, Kaibel, Collitz-Bechtel: αἴζως (i.e. ἔζης); Korhonen: αἴζωσ(εν)\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 5\">line.5: \u003Cspan>Torremuzza, Ferrara, Bertucci, Franz ἔτι α εἴκοσι; Kaibel, Collitz-Bechtel, Korhonen: ἔτια\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5187-5163\">Marta Fogagnolo\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>Markia Loukilia, honest and blameless, lived for 20 years.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>Italian translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5187-5163\">Marta Fogagnolo\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>Markia Loukilia, onesta e irreprensibile, visse 20 anni.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>The epitaph has the traditional structure with the name of the deceased, the epithets \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">χρηστὰ καὶ ἄμεμπτος\u003C/span> (for which, see Korhonen 2004: 84) and the indication of the age, with the verb \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ζάω\u003C/span> in the aorist form. Following Korhonen, the phonetic reading \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">αἴζως\u003C/span> for \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ἔζης\u003C/span> seems to be less probable than \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">αἴζωσ’\u003C/span> or \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">αἴζωσ(εν)\u003C/span> (from \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ζώω\u003C/span>): for a similar form, see Libertini NSA 1931: 391-392 (\u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ἔσζω[σ-]\u003C/span>). Also the reading \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ἔτι α εἴκοσι\u003C/span> seems to be less probable (despite \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ἔτι\u003C/span> of the Christian epitaph Libertini 1931: 45 nr. 10) than the phonetic reading \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ἔτια\u003C/span> (i.g. \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ἔτεα\u003C/span>): see IC IV 168*. The Doricism at l. 3 and the hypercorrection at l. 4 denote the stonecutter’s quest for refinement or poor knowledge of Greek (as also revealed by \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ἔτια\u003C/span> of l. 5).\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Castelli 1769 175 n. 69 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002084\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002084\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Castelli 1784 186 n. 81 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002083\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002083\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Ferrara 1829 352 n. 2 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002005\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002005\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Bertucci 1846 31 n. 6 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002303\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002303\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Franz 1853 5714 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001250\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001250\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Kaibel 1890 \u003Ca href=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\" target=\"_blank\">490\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Hoffmann 1904 5238 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000817\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000817\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Korhonen 2004 108 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. \u003C/div>",[275,278,281,284,286,289,292],{"id":276,"html":277},"editions","\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Μαρκία\n                    Λουκιλία\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Μαρκία\">Μαρκία\u003C/span>  \u0